[Student "S"]
{This is another example of "She who knows, goes."

SOUTH has a solid 18 points, (1 extra for the fifth Club), so when NORTH opens 1NT 
she KNOWS that together they must hold at least 33 points. The may even have 35 points. 

In any case they should be in slam, so SOUTH GOES to 6NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "N:854.K764.862.AJ6 KJ9.AQ.KQJ95.KT4 AQ72.J932.T4.732 T63.T85.A73.Q985"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
